
[1]inducement

   INDU'CEMENT, n. Motive; any thing that leads the mind to will or to
   act; any argument, reason or fact that tends to persuade or influence
   the mind. The love of ease is an inducement to idleness. The love of
   money is an inducement to industry in good men, and to the perpetration
   of crimes in the bad.
